---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="About Us - useUtils" 
  description="Discover the mission behind useUtils. We build beautiful, local-first tools for developers that respect privacy."
  keywords="about useutils, developer tools privacy, secure developer utilities"
>
  <Header />

  <!-- Main Body Content -->
  <main class="flex-grow w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 flex flex-col gap-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-2 pb-6 border-b border-border-hairline/60">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-50 font-sans">
        About us
      </h1>
      <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
        The story and mission behind useUtils: building tools developers actually trust.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      
      <!-- Section 1 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          The Mission
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          Software engineers paste sensitive payloads, API tokens, JWTs, and keys into random online tools every single day. Most web utilities transmit these payloads to remote servers to compile outputs, tracking history, logging keys, and selling metadata. We built <strong class="text-zinc-200">useUtils</strong> to prove that developer utilities can be robust, aesthetically stunning, and completely secure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 2 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Privacy First, by Architecture
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          We don't ask you to trust a written privacy policy blindly. We enforce privacy through our architecture. Every parser, format checker, and key encoder runs entirely client-side using your browser's local sandbox. Zero server transmission.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 3 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Modern Aesthetics
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          Who said developer utilities have to look like layouts from 2005? Drawing inspiration from high-end command line palettes (like Raycast), we styled useUtils to fit cleanly into modern developer workspaces—featuring rich dark charcoal backgrounds, thin razor-sharp borders, syntax coloring, and smooth animations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 4 -->
      <div class="bg-panel border border-border-hairline hover:border-zinc-800 rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 flex flex-col gap-3 transition-colors duration-200">
        <h2 class="text-base font-semibold text-zinc-50 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-2.5">
          <span class="w-1.5 h-4 bg-accent-emerald rounded-full"></span>
          Open and Zero-Dependency
        </h2>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-xs md:text-sm leading-relaxed font-sans">
          Built on a modern stack including Astro, React, and Tailwind CSS, we keep our utilities clean and execute complex parser structures using lightweight, standard web APIs without heavy dependencies.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
